9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><strong>PART 1 â€” What Are Boundaries?</strong></h2>\n<h3 id=\"1-a-day-in-a-boundaryless-life\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#1-a-day-in-a-boundaryless-life\" aria-label=\"1 a day in a boundaryless life permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><strong>1. A Day in a Boundaryless Life</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Key idea:</strong>\nPeople without boundaries feel:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Overwhelmed</li>\n<li>Resentful</li>\n<li>Controlled</li>\n<li>Guilty for saying no</li>\n<li>Responsible for othersâ€™ feelings</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>EI Insight</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Poor boundaries = <strong>emotional fusion</strong></li>\n<li>You feel othersâ€™ emotions as your job to fix</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Warning Signs</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>â€œI donâ€™t want to, but I feel I have toâ€</li>\n<li>Chronic people-pleasing</li>\n<li>Passive resentment</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"2-what-is-a-boundary\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2-what-is-a-boundary\" aria-label=\"2 what is a boundary permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><strong>2. What Is a Boundary?</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Definition:</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A boundary is a property line that defines <strong>where you end and someone else begins</strong>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Boundaries include:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>ğŸ§  Thoughts</li>\n<li>â¤ï¸ Feelings</li>\n<li>ğŸ¯ Choices</li>\n<li>ğŸ•° Time</li>\n<li>ğŸ’° Money</li>\n<li>âš¡ Energy</li>\n<li>ğŸ§â€â™‚ï¸ Body</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>EI Principle</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Emotional maturity = <strong>self-definition without disconnection</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"3-boundary-analogies\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#3-boundary-analogies\" aria-label=\"3 boundary analogies permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><strong>3. Boundary Analogies</strong></h3>\n<p>Boundaries are like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fences with gates</strong> (not walls)</li>\n<li><strong>Skin</strong> (filters, not armor)</li>\n<li><strong>Property lines</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Healthy boundaries</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Let good in</li>\n<li>Keep harm out</li>\n<li>Require <em>intentional choice</em></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"part-2--boundary-conflicts-why-its-hard-to-say-no\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#part-2--boundary-conflicts-why-its-hard-to-say-n